# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project using the Pages Router.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (version added to package.json)
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependency tree

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `frontend/pages/_app.js`**
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component alongside existing `<SpeedInsights />` component
- Placement follows official Vercel documentation for Next.js Pages Router

## Implementation Details

### Documentation Source
Fetched latest installation instructions from: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

### Framework Detection
- Framework: Next.js (version 14.0.0)
- Router: Pages Router (confirmed by presence of `pages/_app.js`)
- Package Manager: npm (confirmed by package-lock.json)

### Integration Approach
Following the official docs for Next.js Pages Router:
1. The Analytics component is imported from `@vercel/analytics/next`
2. Component is placed at the root level in `_app.js` to ensure tracking across all pages
3. Positioned alongside existing SpeedInsights component for consistency

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Verification**: Successfully built the project with `npm run build`
- All 14 pages compiled successfully
- No TypeScript or compilation errors
- Build output shows analytics is properly integrated

✅ **Linter Check**: ESLint not yet configured in this project (setup prompt appeared)
- No breaking changes introduced
- Code follows existing patterns in the file

✅ **Dependency Update**: package-lock.json properly updated with new dependency

## Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the analytics setup:
1. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel project dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy` or push to connected Git repository
3. After deployment, verify analytics tracking by checking browser Network tab for `/_vercel/insights/*` requests
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after user visits accumulate

## Notes
- The project already had `@vercel/speed-insights` installed, so this adds complementary Web Analytics tracking
- Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- No environment variables or additional configuration required
- Analytics will automatically activate once enabled in the Vercel dashboard
